# =============================================================================
# Connext — Root-level environment reference
# =============================================================================
#
# ⚠️  IMPORTANT: A single root .env does NOT work for both apps.
#
#   • Next.js (apps/web) reads .env.local from apps/web/
#   • Express (apps/server) reads .env from apps/server/
#
# Each app must have its own env file. Use the per-app templates:
#
#   apps/web/.env.example    → copy to apps/web/.env.local
#   apps/server/.env.example → copy to apps/server/.env
#
# The shared secrets below (AUTH_SECRET, JWT_SECRET, DATABASE_URL) must be
# identical in both files for the auth bridge to work correctly.
#
# =============================================================================
#
# Quick setup:
#   cp apps/web/.env.example apps/web/.env.local
#   cp apps/server/.env.example apps/server/.env
#   # Then fill in real values in both files
#
# Generate secrets:
#   openssl rand -base64 32
#
# =============================================================================
